<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html>
<head>
<title>mViewer-Help Page</title>
<META http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
<META name="description"
	content="This is the help page for mViewer- a MongoDB UI" />
<LINK rel="SHORTCUT ICON" href="images/icon.png" />
<link href="css/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>
<body width="100%">
	<center>
		<img src="images/index_logo.png" alt="logo" align="center" id="logo">
		<br>
	</center>
	<div class="wrapper">
	<div class="body-cont gen-float">
		<div class="gen-float">
			<div class="left-cont gen-float">
				<div class="list-head">
					<label>Help Options</label>
				</div>
				<ul class="lists">
					<li><a href="#login">Login</a>
					</li>
					<li><a href="#logout">Log out</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="right-cont gen-float">
				<div class="list-head">
					<label id="login">Login</label>
				</div>
				<div class="helpDescription">
				<p>Before logging into the mViewer tool you need to add a user to the <strong>admin</strong> database of the <strong>mongoDB</strong>. To do this first install mongoDB. The installation process for mongoDB can be found <a href="http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Quickstart">here</a>.</p> 
				<p> After <strong>mongoDB</strong> is running. Start the <strong>mongod</strong> process and do the following:
				<img class="helpDescriptionImg" alt="add user " src="images/add_user.png"></img>
				<p> Now you can go to the mViewer login page and fill in the required details.</p>
				</div>    
				<div class="list-head">
					<label id="logout">Log out</label>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>

